WorkItem.Description:
The compiler complains about syntax errors if I declare a class in a function:

function test() {
  // Throws "Expected '}'"
  class ABC {
  }
}

(function () {
  // Throws "Expected '}'     Expected ')'"
  class DEF {
  }
})();


I know that declaring classes in functions are redundant because of the module system. Though the compiler should NOT throw errors.
